.Dd January 28, 2023
.Dt TDFIND 9
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm tdfind ,
.Nd locate a thread by numeric ID
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.In sys/param.h
.In sys/proc.h
.Ft "struct thread *"
.Fn tdfind "lwpid_t tid, pid_t pid"
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Fn pfind
function walks the list of processes in the system, looking for the one with a
process ID of
.Fa pid .
If the process exists, and is not in the zombie state, a pointer to the process
structure will be returned.
.Pp
Both
.Fn pfind
and
.Fn pfind_any
lock the returned process using
.Fn PROC_LOCK "p" .
.Sh RETURN VALUES
.Fn pfind
and
.Fn pfind_any
return a pointer to a
.Vt struct proc
after a successful lookup, and
.Dv NULL
otherwise.
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr pfind 9 ,
.Xr pgfind 9
